Setiap Master Data wajib memiliki:

* Migration
* Model
* Policy
* Blueprint
* Query Object
* Service Object
* Controller
* Routes
* FactoryBot
* Model Spec
* Request Spec
* Policy Spec
* Swagger

---

# 15. Frontend Standard

Setiap Master Data wajib memiliki:

## List Page

* Search
* Status Filter
* Pagination
* Sort
* Create Button
* Edit Button
* Delete Button

---

## Form

* Code
* Name
* Description
* Status

---

# 16. UX Standard

* Code otomatis diubah menjadi uppercase.
* Trim whitespace pada semua input text.
* Validasi ditampilkan secara inline.
* Tombol Save dinonaktifkan saat request berjalan.
* Konfirmasi sebelum Delete.

---

# 17. Authorization

Semua endpoint menggunakan Pundit.

Policy minimal:

* index?
* show?
* create?
* update?
* destroy?

---

# 18. Error Handling

Gunakan standar dari TDD-000.

Semua validation error menggunakan format response yang sama.

---

# 19. Testing Standard

Minimal test:

## Backend

* Model Spec
* Request Spec
* Policy Spec

Coverage:

* ≥80% per file
* Total project ≥90%

## Frontend

* Component Test
* Page Test
* Composable Test

Coverage:

* ≥80% per file
* Total project ≥90%

---

# 20. Definition of Done

Module dianggap selesai apabila:

* Migration berhasil dijalankan.
* CRUD lengkap.
* Search berfungsi.
* Filter berfungsi.
* Pagination berfungsi.
* Sort berfungsi.
* Authorization aktif.
* Blueprint tersedia.
* Swagger diperbarui.
* Factory tersedia.
* Test memenuhi standar coverage.
* RuboCop, Brakeman, ESLint, dan TypeScript lulus.

---

# 21. AI Agent Prompt

Implement Master Data module following:

* TDD-000 Engineering Standards
* TDD-001 Master Data Framework

Generate:

* Migration
* Model
* Query Object
* Service Object
* Policy
* Blueprint
* Controller
* Routes
* FactoryBot
* RSpec
* Swagger Documentation

Business rules:

* Soft delete menggunakan Discard.
* Response menggunakan Blueprinter.
* Search berdasarkan `code` dan `name`.
* Pagination menggunakan Pagy.
* Authorization menggunakan Pundit.
* Tidak menaruh business logic di Controller.
